bscuration at lower redshifts, (c) scaled or unscaled versions of Cygnus\nA at any redshift, and (d) scaled and dust-obscured radio-loud quasars or\ncompact steep spectrum sources. We estimated upper limits on the infrared\nluminosity, the black hole accretion rate, and the star formation rate of IFRS,\nwhich all agreed with corresponding numbers of HzRGs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 9 Jun 2015 12:29:49 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-07-22"}
